summary: good omens isn't promoting satanism, u guys r just weird
body:
good omens isn’t promoting satanism, u guys r just weird

those Christians making that whole petition to cancel good omens is rly not sitting right with me like ok lemme go off for a second ladies n theydies😌

as a chrishtian, y'all got no business doing all of this bc satan lit rally dies like babe that’s the whole Christian agenda right there!

I had my doubts too when I started watching it I thought to myself ok r we rly gonna do this bc I take my religion very seriously.

but then I finished it and it’s not at all what the Good Christians are trying to make it seem. the first thing in every religion is that everybody is worthy of receiving love and giving love, good omens is showing that in various ways, like the literal Antichrist, satans whole fucking son, is capable of love and empathy! it shows that no matter where you came from, you are capable of love!

crowley is a demon, he’s a fallen angel, a Good Christian would read that and put on their look-how-good-I-am-I’m-against-demons-clown outfit and sign that mf petition, but looooooook at crowley for like one second and you’ll see that he’s not like the typical demons the others are, for instance he doesn’t look disgusting and chooses to just annoy people with minor inconveniences instead of Reaping Souls For The Master!

aziraphale, an angel, being able to love and forgive crowley, a demon, is lit rally the height of Christian values and those motherfuckers could only dream of being able to do that.
